  "prompt": "What did you do before a day before JEE advanced?",
  "response": "A day before JEE Advanced, students typically engage in various activities to prepare mentally and physically for the exam. Here are some common things they might do:\n\n1. **Revision**: Many students focus on revising key concepts, formulas, and important topics to ensure they are well-prepared.\n\n2. **Mock Tests**: Some may take a short mock test or practice questions to assess their readiness and identify areas that need a last-minute review.\n\n3. **Relaxation**: To avoid stress, students often take breaks, relax, and indulge in light activities like reading or spending time with family and friends.\n\n4. **Healthy Routine**: Students generally ensure they have a good meal, stay hydrated, and get sufficient sleep to be fresh for the exam day.\n\n5. **Organization**: They may double-check that they have all necessary items ready for the exam day, such as admit cards, stationery, and identification.\n\n6. **Positive Affirmation**: Many engage in motivational talks or practice positive visualization to boost their confidence.\n\nUltimately, the aim is to strike a balance between revising important material and ensuring they are calm and collected for the exam.",
